\label{table:youngasbias}
\end{table}

The proportion of AS elements in the young group of Alu and L1 were compared versus the antisense bias of reference Alu and L1. As has been previously documented, the proportions of AS and S Alu and L1 in the Hg19 reference were significantly different from the null hypothesis of equal distribution (table \ref{table:alul1ref}). A test of equal proportions was used to calculate the deviation from the null hypothesis that young AS RTs occur in equal proportion to that of reference RTs. It was identified that reference Alu and L1 RTs had a significantly different AS bias than newly inserted Alu (proportion AS$_{young}$ = 0.50; proportion AS$_{Ref}$ = 0.59; \num{95}\% CI = \num{-0.12} - \num{-0.057}; p < \num{4.44}e-09). This is evidence that the commonly cited AS bias of reference Alu is not present initially upon integration. 

